full_text: Add a validation check to display a warning message that red cars result in higher premiums, when a red car is added. First, add a new or edit the appropriate validation class. In this example, the object whose color is to be checked is a personal vehicle, so this would be added to the personal vehicle validation class. The method Check Vehicle Color is added to check whether the color of the vehicle is red. If it is red, a warning is added at the default validation level. the vehicle, with the display key, with the vehicle's wizard step, where the problem occurs. The validate-ample method of any validation class calls all the methods in a logical sequence. Add Check Vehicle Color method to validate-ample. Save the changes. Normally, the next step is to invoke the class-based validation. For this example, we do not need to add extra code to the BeforeSave attribute of the vehicle wizard step, since OnVehicle step The exit method calls validate-ample. The exit method calls validate-vehicles step method, which starts validation chaining and eventually validates each vehicle in the Personal Vehicle Validation class. Reload changed classes or restart the server. Select Reload changed classes. Log into Policy Center as Alice Applegate. Add a vehicle with color red on the vehicle's step of a personal auto submission. Click Next.
